text: Is there a dream you're nurturing that you haven't shared with me yet?
Which part of yourself do you feel I understand the least?
Can you describe a time in your life when you felt most authentically yourself?
What are you most passionate about right now, and what fuels that passion?
Are you facing any challenges currently that I might not be aware of?
Share a childhood memory that you feel significantly shaped who you are today.
How would you define 'happiness' for yourself in this current phase of your life?
Reflecting on your upbringing, is there anything you hope to do differently, or perhaps emulate?
What accomplishment, big or small, are you most proud of recently?
Which value do you hold most dear, and how does it guide your decisions?
How do you personally define success for yourself at this point?
Is there something about your adult life you wish I had a better understanding of?
What kind of support from me do you find most meaningful or helpful now?
In what ways do you feel genuinely loved and appreciated by me and others?
Do you have any fears or anxieties about your own future?
How has your perception of our relationship evolved as you've gotten older?
Can you recall a piece of advice I once gave you that actually stuck or proved useful?
What have you learned about the world that has genuinely surprised you?
Which activities or circumstances bring you the greatest sense of peace or contentment?
If you could tell me one thing completely unfiltered, what would it be?
